Hello,

We have neo vortex with solo adapter and Sparkmax mounted on a shaft for our elevator.
When we enable it, it doesn’t start automatically.
But a little manual push is helping it.

drive.google.com

Google Drive file.

Any thoughts/suggestion on what we may be missing ?

Thanks

Do you have a current limit on the motor controller? It sounds like the torque of the motor is not enough to actually get your mechanism moving, but once it starts moving, the motor can keep it moving. If that’s what it is, increasing your current limit should fix it.

Okay, I just checked it, the default sparkmax current limit should be 80 amps. That’s pretty high.

docs.revrobotics.com

SPARK MAX Configuration Parameters | REV ION Brushless

If your current is actually spiking that high and still not moving the mechanism, you would need to see why there is so much friction in your system. Or maybe see if you need to gear your motor higher. You should be able to check your output current with getOutputCurrent() in the sparkmax library.

That is typical behavior when one of the 3 phases is not working. A 3-phase motor will sort of work when connected to only 2 of the phases. It may be as simple as one of the three output connections from the Sparkmax being bad to an internal open circuit.
